article.headline: Smith's 32 points helps Lynx break losing streak
article.linkText: Smith cans seven 3-pointers in Lynx win over Storm
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) _ Katie Smith scored 32 points and tied WNBA
records with five 3-pointers in a half and seven overall in
Minnesota's 77-72 victory over Seattle on Saturday night.
	   The Lynx (4-4) broke a three-game losing streak and stopped the
Storm's winning streak at three.
	   Smith hit back-to-back 3s to start a 15-2 run midway through the
first half. Seattle didn't adjust its defense and Smith continued
to knock down open shots. She finished the half with 19 points on
7-for-10 shooting, including 5-for-5 from 3-point range.
	   Seattle didn't do much better in stopping Smith's teammates.
Minnesota shot 62.5 percent (20-for-32) and 70 percent (7-for-10)
from 3-point range and held a 48-35 lead at halftime.
	   Seattle (3-4) fought back behind the play of Lauren Jackson, who
scored 14 of her 18 points in the second half. Seattle cut the lead
to two with two minutes to play, but Smith responded by making 3 of
4 free throws in the final minute to seal the victory.
	   Smith finished 11-for-20 from the field and 7-for-10 from
3-point range. She was the sixth WNBA player to make seven
3-pointers in a game. The most recent was Portland's Sophia
Witherspoon on June 29, 2001.
	   The Lynx shot 47.6 percent overall and 52.9 percent on
3-pointers. Seattle was 30-of-62 and 7-of-9 from 3-point range.
	   Tamika Williams scored 12 points and grabbed nine rebounds for
Minnesota. Sheri Sam scored 11 points.
	   Sue Bird had 16 for Seattle, and Kamila Vodichkova added 12.
	   Minnesota outrebounded Seattle 33-26.<
^Notes:@ Seattle went 3-2 on its five-game homestand. ... The
Storm's three-game winning streak was the second longest active run
behind Los Angeles' nine consecutive victories.
